<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER RT-610 SERIES - INSTALL - MAIN DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="6">
        <title>MAIN DRIVE GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If previously removed, install the bushing in the pocket of the input shaft. Install flush
                with the shaft, making sure that the oil hole in the shaft is not plugged (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024f3">Figure 153</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024f3" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024f3" filename="../figg13/G13024F3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 153. Install Bushing in Pocket of Input Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the input shaft in the splines of the drive gear, moving the gear forward against
                the inside wall of the case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024f4">Figure 154</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024f4" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024f4" filename="../figg13/G13024F4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 154. Install Input Shaft in Splines of Drive Gear</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the snap ring in the groove in the I.D. of the drive gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024f5">Figure 155</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024f5" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024f5" filename="../figg13/G13024F5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 155. Install Snap Ring in Groove</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the drive gear spacer on the shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024f6">Figure 156</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024f6" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024f6" filename="../figg13/G13024F6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 156. Install Drive Gear Spacer on Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the drive gear bearing on the shaft and into the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024f7">Figure 157</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024f7" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024f7" filename="../figg13/G13024F7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 157. Install Drive Gear Bearing on Shaft</caption>
        </figure>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bearing retaining snap ring in the groove in the input shaft, taper to the
                outside (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13024f8">Figure 158</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <figure id="f13024f8" figsize="col-wide">
            <graphic id="g13024f8" filename="../figg13/G13024F8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
            <caption>Figure 158. Install Bearing Retaining Snap Ring</caption>
        </figure>
    </svcproc>
